NEWCAP
  Move your capital to a new sector.

SYNTAX
  newcap <x,y>

DESCRIPTION
  Relocates your capital to the specified sector.  All relative
  coordinates for your country shift so that the new capital becomes
  (0,0).

  The new capital sector must be:
    - Owned by you
    - Designated as capital type ('c')

  After moving, all sector coordinates shown in census, map, and
  other commands are relative to the new capital.

  WARNING: Moving the capital changes all your sector coordinates.
  Update your thresholds and delivery settings if needed.

EXAMPLE
  newcap 2,0                move capital to the sector at current 2,0

SEE ALSO
  capital  designate  census  map
